00:00:37.500 --> 00:00:40.400
So, if you read
the Oxford dictionary,

00:00:40.400 --> 00:00:43.100
it says that meditation
is thinking in silence.

00:00:43.100 --> 00:00:46.000
Now first of all,
you cannot think aloud

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:51.500
and secondly thinking is of course
the exact opposite of what meditation is,

00:00:51.500 --> 00:00:53.500
as originally conceived in the East.

00:00:54.460 --> 00:00:55.480
So meditation,

00:00:55.500 --> 00:00:59.000
Patanjali was one of the first
to talk about meditation

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:02.700
and he said that meditation
is the cessation of thinking,

00:01:02.700 --> 00:01:05.800
it's the stopping of your thoughts,
it's the control of your thoughts,

00:01:05.800 --> 00:01:08.000
the control of your attention.

00:01:08.500 --> 00:01:13.100
In the West we know there are
three states of consciousness,

00:01:13.100 --> 00:01:15.600
that's sleeping,
dreaming and thinking.

00:01:15.600 --> 00:01:17.500
But in the East,

00:01:17.500 --> 00:01:21.000
and we think that thinking is
the highest state of consciousness,

00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:25.000
but in the East it's very common knowledge
that there's another state of consciousness

00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:27.000
It's called
the fourth state of consciousness.

00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:28.000
Turiya awastha

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:33.000
and the fourth state of consciousness
is the state of Thoughtless Awareness.

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:34.000
Mental Silence.

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:37.000
Where you learn
to stop your thinking.

00:01:37.000 --> 00:01:40.000
And this process of stopping your thinking

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:44.000
has amazing benefits at the subjective level

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:47.000
but also objectively and you feel,

00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:51.000
when your thoughts are stopped you feel happy,

00:01:51.000 --> 00:01:54.000
you feel joy and depending on the intensity,

00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:56.000
you can feel absolute bliss.

00:01:56.000 --> 00:01:59.000
So there are several subjective correlates,

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:01.000
what you feel when you meditate,

00:02:01.000 --> 00:02:02.000
which are listed here

00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:05.000
and which, however, have health implications.

